.TH rubik "" "" Command
.PC "Play Rubik's cube"
.B /usr/games/rubik
.PP
The command
.B rubik
lets you fiddle with an electronic version of Rubik's cube.
By issuing commands, you can ``rotate'' the segments of the virtual cube and,
with some agony, align all the ``colors''.
.PP
.B rubik
is written in
.BR m4 ,
and is a good example of extended programming in this utility.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "commands," commands
.Xr "m4" m4
